{{Infobox rockunit | name = Chandler Formation | image = | caption = | type = [[Geological formation]] | age = [[Early Jurassic]] ([[Hettangian]]) | prilithology = | otherlithology = | namedfor = | namedby = | region = [[Baffin Island]] ([[Crimmins Island]]) | country =[[Canada]] {{Flag|Canada}} | coordinates = | unitof = | subunits = | underlies =[[Bravo Lake Formation]] | overlies = | thickness = | extent = | area = | map = | map_caption = }}
The '''Chandler Formation''' is a [[Mesozoic]] geologic [[Formation (geology)|formation]]. [[Dinosaur]] remains are among the fossils that have been recovered from the formation, although none have yet been referred to a specific [[genus]].<ref name="dinosaurdistribution">Weishampel, et al. (2004). "Dinosaur distribution." Pp. 517-607.</ref>
