[[File:A fire lighting.jpg|thumb|A fire kindled from firelighter blocks surrounded by [[briquette]]s inside a [[stove]].]]

A '''firelighter''' is a small, [[solid fuel]] tablet for [[fire making]]. Firelighters marketed as [[consumer products]] may be used to start a wood or coal fire in a [[fireplace]], [[wood-burning stove]], or [[Portable stove#Solid-fuel stoves|solid-fuel portable stove]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://dictionary.cambridge.org/dictionary/british/firelighter|work=Cambridge Dictionary|title=firelighter|publisher=[[Cambridge University Press]]|accessdate=14 June 2012|quote=(a small block of) material which burns very easily and is used for helping to start wood or coal fires}}</ref>

As a [[hazardous material]], firelighters are assigned a [[UN number]]: [[List of UN numbers 2601 to 2700|2623]] ("Firelighters; solid with [[flammable liquid]]").

