==Illinois== [[Hurricane Audrey]] directed moisture up to a front to its north across the Midwest during late June 1957 as it transitioned into an [[extratropical cyclone]]. Heavy rains fell across central Illinois, leading to the wettest known event to be associated with a tropical cyclone or its remains across [[Illinois]].<ref name="Audrey">{{cite book|author2=Hydrometeorological Prediction Center|url=http://www.wpc.ncep.noaa.gov/tropical/rain/audrey1957.html|chapter=Hurricane Audrey rainfall page|title=Tropical Cyclone Point Maxima|author=Roth, David M|date=April 22, 2010|accessdate=April 24, 2010}}</ref> [[Image:Paine 01 oct 1986 2218Z.jpg|thumb|right|250 px|Hurricane Paine (1986)]]
