e Bob (1979)|Bob 1979]] || [[Edwardsport, Indiana|Edwardsport Power Plant]] ||<ref name="Mid West"/> |- | 9 || 131.1 || 5.16 || [[Hurricane Katrina|Katrina 2005]] || [[Hanover, Indiana|Hanover Radio]] ||<ref name="Mid West"/> |- | 10 || 121.4 || 4.78 || [[Tropical Storm Debra (1978)|Debra 1978]] || [[Crane, Indiana|Crane NSA]] ||<ref name="Mid West"/> |- |} {{clear}}
==Iowa== Hurricane Carla was a large hurricane that moved into Texas during September 1961. As it transitioned into an [[extratropical cyclone]] across the [[Great Plains]] and Midwest, heavy rain fell in a band on the poleward side of a frontal boundary extending northeast from Carla, leading to the wettest known event to be associated with a tropical cyclone or its remains across [[Iowa]].<ref name="Mid West"/> [[File:Hurricane Carla Satellite.JPG|thumb|right|250 px|Hurricane Carla]]
