==Missouri== Remnant tropical cyclones can move into the state which originate in either the Pacific or Atlantic hurricane basins. [[Tropical Storm Erin (2007)|Tropical Storm Erin]] reintensified over [[Oklahoma]] leading to heavy rainfall in that state. As the system moved eastward, its surface low quickly dissipated. However, its mid-level circulation remained robust, leading to a burst of heavy rainfall across [[Missouri]] exceeding {{convert|10|in|mm}} in isolated spots, which became the wettest tropical cyclone remnant on record for the state.<ref name="Mid Atl"/><ref name="ERIN">{{cite web|author=David M. Roth|url=http://www.wpc.ncep.noaa.gov/tropical/rain/erin2007.html|title=Tropical Storm Erin Rainfall Page|accessdate=March 6, 2008}}</ref> [[Image:Tropical Depression Erin inland over OK.png|thumb|right|250 px|Tropical Storm Erin (2007)]]
