==Oklahoma== Remnant tropical cyclones can move into the state which originate in either the Pacific or Atlantic hurricane basins. In 2007, [[Tropical Storm Erin (2007)|Tropical Storm Erin]] reintensified over [[Oklahoma]] leading to heavy rainfall within the state. Rainfall exceeded {{convert|12|in|mm}} in isolated spots, which turned out to be the third wettest tropical cyclone remnant on record for Oklahoma.<ref name="WPCGULF"/><ref name="ERIN"/> [[Image:Bill 2015-06-16 1955Z.jpg|thumb|right|250 px|Tropical Storm Bill (2015)]]
