==Pennsylvania== Although Hurricane Agnes was barely a hurricane at landfall in [[Florida]], its major impact was over the Mid-Atlantic region, where Agnes combined with a non-tropical low to produce widespread rains of {{convert|6|to|12|in|mm}} with local amounts up to {{convert|19|in|mm}} in western [[Schuylkill County, Pennsylvania|Schuylkill County]] in [[Pennsylvania]].<ref name="WPCMAX"/> These rains produced widespread severe flooding from [[Virginia]] northward to New York, with other flooding occurring over the western portions of the Carolinas. [[Image:Agnes2.jpg|thumb|right|250px|Hurricane Agnes over Pennsylvania]] {{Wettest tropical cyclones in Pennsylvania|align=left}} {{Clear}}
==Puerto Rico== [[Puerto Rico]] has seen dramatic rainfall from tropical cyclones and their precursor disturbances. The most recent tropical cyclone-related deluge was from [[Hurricane Irene]] in August 2011, when {{convert|22.05|in|mm}} of rain was measured at Gurabo Abajo.<ref>{{Cite book|publisher=United States National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration's National Weather Service|author=Roth, David M|url=http://www.wpc.ncep.noaa.gov/tropical/rain/georges1998.html|chapter=Hurricane Georges|author2=Hydrometeorological Prediction Center|title=Tropical Cyclone Point Maxima|accessdate=June 6, 2012}}</ref> The heaviest rainfall noted over the past 30&nbsp;years was from the precursor disturbance to [[1985 Atlantic hurricane season#Tropical Storm Isabel|Tropical Storm Isabel]], when {{convert|31.67|in|mm}} fell at Toro Negro Forest.<ref>{{Cite book|publisher=United States National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration's National Weather Service|author=Roth, David M|author2=Hydrometeorological Prediction Center|url=http://www.wpc.ncep.noaa.gov/tropical/rain/isabel1985.html|chapter=Tropical Storm Isabel|title=Tropical Cyclone Point Maxima|accessdate=June 6, 2012}}</ref> [[Hurricane Eloise]] of 1975 dropped {{convert|33.29|in|mm}} of rainfall at Dos Bocas, with {{convert|23.07|in|mm}} falling in 24&nbsp;hours. [[Image:Maria 2017-09-19 2015Z.png|thumb|right|250px|Hurricane Maria]] {{Wettest tropical cyclones in Puerto Rico|align=left}} {{Clear}}
==Rhode Island== The flood from [[Hurricane Diane]] led to a significant death toll (nearly 200) from Pennsylvania eastward through southern New England.<ref name=Diane/> [[Image:Hurricane Bob 19 aug 1991 1226Z.jpg|thumb|right|250 px|Hurricane Bob]]
