==South Carolina== Portions of [[South Carolina]] experienced significant rainfall totals approaching {{convert|24|in|mm}} with [[Hurricane Florence]], which became the wettest known tropical cyclone to impact the state. The flash flooding covered numerous roadways and washed out bridges, with the statewide transportation damage totaling at least {{ntsp|38000000000||US$}}. River flooding was great across the state. In addition, the rainfall broke dams, flooded houses, and covered fields. [[File:Florence 2018-09-13 1550Z.jpg|thumb|right|250px|Hurricane Florence]]
