==Tennessee== [[Tropical Storm Chris (1982)|Tropical Storm Chris]] moved inland into the Southeast, producing a burst of rainfall across Tennessee exceeding {{convert|13|in|mm}}.<ref>{{cite book|author=Roth, David M|title=Tropical Cyclone Point Maxima|url=http://www.wpc.ncep.noaa.gov/tropical/rain/chris1982.html|chapter=Tropical Storm Chris rainfall page|accessdate=June 7, 2012|author2=Hydrometeorological Prediction Center|publisher=United States National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration's National Weather Service}}</ref> This system stands as Tennessee's wettest known tropical cyclone.<ref name="WPCSE"/> [[File:Chris 1982-09-11 1515Z.png|thumb|right|250 px|Tropical Storm Chris (1982)]]
