==United States Virgin Islands== [[File:Hortense 1996-09-12 1915Z.png|thumb|right|250 px|Hurricane Hortense (1996)]] Tropical cyclones affect these islands of the northeast Caribbean on a regular basis. [[Hurricane Hortense]] is the wettest known system for the U. S. Virgin Islands, bringing over {{convert|18|in|mm}} of rainfall.<ref name="Hortense">{{cite book|author=Roth, David M|author2=Hydrometeorological Prediction Center|title=Tropical Cyclone Point Maxima|publisher=United States National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration's National Weather Service|chapter=Hurricane Hortense|url=http://www.wpc.ncep.noaa.gov/tropical/rain/hortense1996.html|accessdate=June 4, 2012}}</ref>
